{
  "stem": "27390.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It-- it was-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] when the war-- when-- a few weeks before the war broke out, we were still on holiday in the country, like I told you.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We lived in the country and my father was-- it was he could see it's going to happen sooner or later so he managed to get a-- a wholesome car to take us back to-- to town.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[DRINKS] And when we came back to Lodz, was already, the Polish government requisitioned all the modes of transport, horses and carriages and cars and taxis.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everything was requisitioned and there was already general mobilization.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we started digging trenches in the streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know what for but [LAUGHS] we were told to dig trenches.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were giving-- they didn't have enough gas masks for the population.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they told us if we take, buy something like cotton candies and we dip it in bicarbonated soda and you put it on your face like the doctors wear in the hospital, such a mask, and this will protect us from a gas attack.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So everybody started making up these artificial gas masks and we were told to put-- I suppose the same thing happened here-- on the windows to put the cross with sticky paper, white sticky paper for when the window shatter it shouldn't-- and also a lot of black material was being sold to cover over the windows, the light shouldn't show in the street.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we were getting ready for-- for war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Polish government, the radio was-- it was censored.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It wasn't a free radio.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they were telling us how strong they are and how many tanks they have and how many planes they have.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
